    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1978-09-17T13:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1978-09-17T12:40:00-05:00" n="56"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d56">
                <head>56. Handwritten Note Prepared by the Ambassador to Israel (<persName
                        corresp="#p_LSW_1">Lewis</persName>)<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d56fn1">Source: Department of State, <gloss target="#t_US_1"
                            >U.S.</gloss> Embassy Tel Aviv, Principal Officer Program Files, Lot
                        85F104, Personal for Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_LSW_1"
                            >Lewis</persName>—Sensitive Notes 1978. No classification marking. See
                            <ref target="#d28fn90">footnote 90, Document 28</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Camp David</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            from="1978-09-17T13:40:00-04:00" to="1978-09-17T14:30:00-04:00"
                            >September 17, 1978, 1:40–2:30 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_LSW_1"
                        >Lewis</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_SHH_1">Saunders</persName>,
                        <persName corresp="#p_BA_2">Barak</persName>/<persName corresp="#p_DM_2"
                        >Dayan</persName>— + <persName corresp="#p_CJE_2">Carter</persName>, et.
                    al.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <gloss target="#t_CV_1">CV</gloss>
                    </hi>—I’ll try to see if there is a way to handle the Jerusalem letter in a less
                    open way.</p>
                <pb facs="0238" n="203" xml:id="pg_203"/>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <persName corresp="#p_DM_2">Dayan</persName>
                    </hi>—This letter in this form will just <hi rend="italic">be</hi> the end of
                    the Conference. Jerusalem too sensitive. Had it been about Gaza, well, <hi
                        rend="italic">possibly.</hi> (grimaces.) But you’re not insisting on stating
                    your views now on settlements, etc.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_BA_2">Barak</persName> (after talking to <persName
                        corresp="#p_BM_2">Begin</persName>)—OK we accept “shall govern
                    themselves”—but want it clear in the minutes of the meeting that Israeli
                    interpretation of the phrase will by [be?] “shall govern themselves through
                    their autonomous institutions.”</p>
                <p>(<persName corresp="#p_MW_1">Mondale</persName> &amp; <persName corresp="#p_JH_1"
                        >Jordan</persName> + <persName corresp="#p_DS_1">Dinitz</persName>
                    enter)</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <persName corresp="#p_DM_2">Dayan</persName>:</hi> (Restates position on
                    letter to <persName corresp="#p_MW_1">Mondale</persName>).</p>
                <p>(<persName corresp="#p_DM_2">Dayan</persName> &amp; <persName corresp="#p_BA_2"
                        >Barak</persName> insist none of them heard Pres. talk last night about this
                    letter—if so, would be impossible.)</p>
                <p>(<hi rend="italic">
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJE_2">Carter</persName>
                    </hi> enters)</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_JC_1">JC</gloss>—<persName corresp="#p_SA_1">Sadat</persName>
                    this morning said he could accept placement permanence of <gloss
                        target="#t_UN_1">UN</gloss> forces in Raffah, if <gloss target="#t_GOI_1"
                        >GOI</gloss> had perm. <gloss target="#t_UN_1">UN</gloss> observers on their
                    side &amp; be flex. on Jerusalem. I said they <hi rend="italic">can’t</hi> be.
                    He said perhaps he could delete, if exchange of letters. We can word them as
                    moderate as possible, re-endorse <gloss target="#t_UN_1">UN</gloss> resolutions
                    we have voted for.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_MD_1">MD</gloss>—Argues against <hi rend="italic">any</hi>
                    restatement of US position.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_JC_1">JC</gloss>—I can’t go back on my promise to <persName
                        corresp="#p_SA_1">Sadat</persName>. I’m willing to let <persName
                        corresp="#p_BA_2">Barak</persName> &amp; <gloss target="#t_Cy_1">Cy</gloss>
                    work on wording, however.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_MD_1">MD</gloss>—OK. But let me review problem of “occupied
                    territory” language. Reviews Mt. Scopus, Hadassah, Wailing Wall, Jewish quarter
                    history. They took it, we took it back. We have our position—&amp; when time
                    comes we’ll negotiate about it. But for you to propose to restate</p>
                <p>I have nothing to suggest.But for first time at Camp David, we’ve been presented
                    with a statement of <hi rend="italic">your</hi> position—we didn’t come here to
                    argue with <hi rend="italic">you</hi> over Jerusalem.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_JC_1">JC</gloss>—Well. I understand your position. <persName
                        corresp="#p_SA_1">Sadat</persName> has frequently said here that he doesn’t
                    contemplate return of all East to Arabs.</p>
                <p>But we need to work on this.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <persName corresp="#p_BA_2">Barak</persName>:</hi> Why doesn’t <persName
                        corresp="#p_SA_1">Sadat</persName> state his position in his letter, &amp;
                    express in it <hi rend="italic">your</hi> position? And you just send it to
                    us.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <gloss target="#t_CV_1">CV</gloss>
                    </hi>—Maybe we could merely refer to statements made by Yost, Scranton, &amp;
                        <persName corresp="#p_YAJ_1">Young</persName>.<note n="2" xml:id="d56fn2"
                        >References are to Charles W. Yost, who served as Representative to the
                        United Nations from January 1969 until February 1971; William W. Scranton,
                        Representative to the United Nations from March 1976 until January 1977; and
                            <persName corresp="#p_YAJ_1">Andrew Young</persName>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Discussion <persName corresp="#p_DM_2">Dayan</persName>/<persName
                        corresp="#p_CJE_2">Carter</persName>—re definitions of East Jerusalem,
                    etc.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJE_2">Carter</persName>
                    </hi>—You can’t deny us right to state <hi rend="italic">our</hi> position. We
                    might qualify our statement re Holy Places, etc.</p>
                <pb facs="0239" n="204" xml:id="pg_204"/>
                <p>I’m willing to work with you, but can’t violate my promise to <persName
                        corresp="#p_SA_1">Sadat</persName>.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_MD_1">MD</gloss>—But not at Camp David! Had we known we had to
                    argue <hi rend="italic">here</hi> with you over Jerusalem, we wouldn’t have
                    come! This for first time, 4 hours before the end, we’re presented with US
                    position which will be totally negative.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">All</hi> our agreements over settlements are not nearly as
                    important as this letter over Jerusalem.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_MD_1">MD</gloss>—makes distinction again re certain places in
                    East Jerusalem.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_JC_1">JC</gloss>—Sit with <persName corresp="#p_CJE_2"
                        >Carter</persName> &amp; draft. If can’t accept, then let’s adjourn.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_MD_1">MD</gloss>—I don’t know. <hi rend="italic">Perhaps</hi>
                    only referring to this point might sell. I really don’t know.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sinai</hi>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_JC_1">JC</gloss>—Do you agree that <gloss target="#t_UN_1"
                        >UN</gloss> observers on your side would also <hi rend="italic">not</hi> be
                    withdrawn without <gloss target="#t_SC_1">SC</gloss> approval?</p>
                <p>Ezer—<hi rend="italic">Yes.</hi>
                    <note n="3" xml:id="d56fn3">At the top of the page, <persName corresp="#p_LSW_1"
                            >Lewis</persName> wrote that <persName corresp="#p_WE_1"
                            >Weizman</persName> entered the room at 2:05 p.m.</note>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_JC_1">JC</gloss>—<persName corresp="#p_SA_1">Sadat</persName>
                    doesn’t want El-Arish, when under Egyptian flag, for negotiations.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_JC_1">JC</gloss>—<persName corresp="#p_SA_1">Sadat</persName>
                    has given on internat’l waterway. Won’t accelerate dip. rel. beyond 9 months
                    initial completion of withdrawal.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_MD_1">MD</gloss>—What happens after Camp David?</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_JC_1">JC</gloss>—Re Oct. 24 deadline, <hi rend="italic"
                        >if</hi> Knesset agrees to remove settlements, he will extend. If not, he
                    will go to <gloss target="#t_UNSC_1">UNSC</gloss>.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_SA_1">Sadat</persName> wants get Knesset debate over <hi
                        rend="italic">before</hi> negotiations. Meanwhile, make arrangements.
                        <persName corresp="#p_BM_2">Begin</persName> said 2 weeks. <gloss
                        target="#t_MD_1">MD</gloss> said perhaps, but could go a <hi rend="italic"
                        >little longer.</hi>
                </p>
            </div>
